  "prompt": "What are some good movies about a person that has a hidden power that he/she couldn't use until put into a pressure situation?",
  "response": "There are numerous films that explore the theme of a character discovering or unlocking a hidden power when faced with extraordinary circumstances. Here are some notable examples:\n\n1. **\"The Matrix\" (1999)**  \n   - Neo (Keanu Reeves) discovers he is \"The One\" with extraordinary abilities within the simulated reality of the Matrix, but only after being pushed to the limit in a high-pressure situation.\n\n2. **\"Chronicle\" (2012)**  \n   - Three teenagers gain telekinetic powers after encountering a mysterious object. The protagonist, Andrew (Dane DeHaan), experiences a dramatic evolution of his abilities under intense emotional and physical pressure.\n\n3. **\"Unbreakable\" (2000)**  \n   - David Dunn (Bruce Willis) slowly discovers he has superhuman strength and resilience after surviving a train crash. His abilities are tested as he confronts a dangerous antagonist.\n\n4. **\"Lucy\" (2014)**  \n   - Lucy (Scarlett Johansson) gains increasingly powerful mental and physical abilities after a drug unlocks her brain's full potential, forcing her to face life-threatening situations.\n\n5. **\"Carrie\" (1976 or 2013)**  \n   - Carrie White (Sissy Spacek or Chlo\u00eb Grace Moretz) discovers her telekinetic powers during moments of extreme emotional stress, culminating in a tragic and explosive climax.\n\n6. **\"Spider-Man\" (2002)**  \n   - Peter Parker (Tobey Maguire) gains superpowers after being bitten by a radioactive spider but only learns to harness his abilities after the death of his uncle and the pressure of fighting crime.\n\n7. **\"Jumper\" (2008)**  \n   - David Rice (Hayden Christensen) discovers he can teleport, a power he uses to escape danger and confront threats from a secret organization.\n\n8. **\"The Dark Knight Rises\" (2012)**  \n   - Bruce Wayne (Christian Bale) must push himself beyond his limits to regain his strength and confront Bane, rediscovering his inner power and determination in the process.\n\n9. **\"Looper\" (2012)**  \n   - Joe (Joseph Gordon-Levitt) discovers unexpected abilities when faced with the challenge of confronting his future self and protecting a child with latent telekinetic powers.\n\n10. **\"X-Men: First Class\" (2011)**  \n    - Charles Xavier (James McAvoy) and Erik Lehnsherr (Michael Fassbender) help other mutants harness their powers, with many characters discovering their abilities in high-stakes situations.\n\nThese films often focus on the psychological and emotional journey of the characters as they learn to control or embrace their newfound powers, making them compelling and relatable stories.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
